Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The Center is incorporated under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code (the "Code") and, accordingly, is exempt from federal income taxes on related income pursuant to Section 501(a) of the Code. The Center is classified as a public charity. In accordance with generally accepted accounting principles, the Center annually evaluates its tax status and tax positions taken with respect to its operations and financial position.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Management works with the Organization's external auditors to ensure the complete and accurate preparation of the Form. Management provides the 990 to the board for review prior to signature and submission.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The center ensures that the conflict of interest policy is enforced by requiring board members to sign conflict of interest documents on a yearly basis. These documents are reviewed annually by management to identify any conflicts, actual or perceived, and to develop necessary resolutions for any identified conflicts.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The board of directors approves compensation after careful review of other similar organizations' compensation packages.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Center provides these forms and documents upon written request.
Part XI, line 2c explanation: The process has not changed from prior year.
